text: Kwhlosothar Rural Municipality is one of the local level of Lamjung District out of 8 local levels. It has 9 wards and according to 2011 Nepal census, 10,032 people live there. It has area. Its center is in the office of previous Maling V.D.C. Besisahar Municipality; Marsyandi Rural Municipality are in the east, Kaski District is in the west, Kaski District and Marsyandi Rural Municipality are in the north and Madhya Nepal Municipality and Besisahar Municipality are in the south of Kwhlosothar Rural Municipality. Previous Baglungpani V.D.C. (1,2,5 & 6 wards), previous Maling V.D.C. (all wards), previous Uttarkanya V.D.C. (all wards), previous Bhujung V.D.C. (all wards), previous Pasagaun V.D.C (all wards), previous Bhoje V.D.C (all wards) and previous Gilung V.D.C. (all wards) are included in this newly made rural municipality. title: Kwhlosothar Rural Municipality
